source.name: 2006-2010 American Community Survey  5-Year Selected Population Tables
source.description: The 2006-2010 ACS 5-Year Selected Population Tables (SPT) use ACS data aggregated over a 5-year period to provide more reliable estimates of detailed social, economic, and housing characteristics for many race, tribal, Hispanic, and ancestry population groups at multiple levels of geography. Detailed tables on topics such as educational attainment, fertility, nativity, citizenship, income, poverty, and homeownership are iterated for many racial and ethnic population groups.  For the SPT, detailed tables are presented for up to 392 population groups in geographies down to the tract level where population thresholds were met.
